### Variables (ajusta host y token si aplica)
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api

### 1) Importar por URL Amazon (ruta plana)
# Respuesta 200 (ejemplo): { "id":"uuid", "source":"AMAZON", "sourceId":"B08N5WRWNW", "title":"...",
#   "mainImageUrl":"https://...", "basePriceUsd":29.99, "localPath":"/product/amazon/B08N5WRWNW",
#   "apiPath":"/api/product/amazon/B08N5WRWNW", "pricing":{ "finalPriceLocal":12345.67, ... },
#   "warnings":[], "alreadyImported":false }
POST {{baseUrl}}/import-product
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "url": "https://www.amazon.com/dp/B08N5WRWNW",
  "forceRefresh": false
}

### 1b) Mismo endpoint usando `input` (texto pegado en buscador)
POST {{baseUrl}}/import-product
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "input": "https://www.amazon.com/dp/B08N5WRWNW"
}

### 2) Ficha JSON (misma ruta que usa el SPA /product/amazon/:asin)
GET {{baseUrl}}/product/amazon/B08N5WRWNW

### 3) Búsqueda híbrida: URL → importa; texto → catálogo local
POST {{baseUrl}}/imported-products/hybrid-search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "q": "auriculares"
}

### 4) Refrescar precio desde PA-API (id = UUID del producto importado)
POST {{baseUrl}}/imported-products/UUID_AQUI/revalidate
Content-Type: application/json

{}
